    "extract": "The Alpena Flyer was an American automobile manufactured between 15 June 1910 and 1914 in Alpena, Michigan by the Alpena Motor Car Company. Approximately 480 cars in 13 models were produced, costing around $1,500, and only one remaining car is known to exist today. The car was intended to be light and inexpensive, and to make Alpena into an \"Automobile City\"."
